# SSH config (tracked, public). Host-specific details that shouldn't be
# published — HostName, Tailscale tailnet/MagicDNS names, internal hostnames —
# live in the untracked companion ~/.ssh/config.local, pulled in via the
# Include below. Relative Include paths resolve against ~/.ssh, so this works
# even though this file is a symlink into the dotfiles repo.
#
# See ssh/config.local.example for the expected shape. `dots doctor` verifies
# the local file exists (manifest `requires_local`); a gitleaks rule blocks any
# *.ts.net name from being committed into this public repo.
Include config.local

# Synology NAS (DS420+). Key auth via ~/.ssh/id_synology. Set up 2026-05-21.
# HostName lives in config.local (Tailscale MagicDNS name, kept out of this
# public repo). `ssh zachnas` works on the home LAN and off-LAN.
Host zachnas
	User zachkysar
	Port 22
	IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_synology
	IdentitiesOnly yes
